Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Software Engineer position with NetApp. I bring over three years of professional experience in system programming, storage systems, and data management solutions, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed and developed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that seamlessly handled file operations across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO via expiring signed URLs — giving me direct, hands-on experience with storage systems and data management solutions that align with NetApp's intelligent data infrastructure mission. I developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions to handle long-running data import jobs and prevent Lambda timeouts, applying system programming principles for reliable execution. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications, where I focused on writing efficient, maintainable, and reusable code. More recently, as a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected an MCP AI interaction layer translating natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1000+ platform endpoints, implementing rigorous API contract design, input validation, and safe execution across distributed microservices. I built an observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks to troubleshoot complex issues and track quality. I also optimized system performance via prompt routing and agent concurrency, reducing latency by 60% and LLM costs by 50% — demonstrating the performance tuning and optimization skills this role requires. Together, these roles have prepared me to design, develop, and maintain software for storage and data management solutions and contribute meaningfully to NetApp's core engineering responsibilities.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in system-level programming, performance optimization, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture NetApp values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion, leveraging CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster for model training and fine-tuning, applying performance tuning techniques for GPU-accelerated computing. I was responsible for managing the full model development lifecycle, implementing model inference with vLLM and Hugging Face deployment with a focus on performance optimization. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents with LangChain, for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the communication and teamwork skills central to this role. Additionally, my personal project, Dark Factory, demonstrates deep operating systems knowledge through system-level programming: I implemented full ownership of CLI IO via PTY to check and log every command before execution by bash shell, and provided event-driven agentic loops that broadcast real-time updates, eliminating polling overhead through performance optimization techniques. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to NetApp's team and mission.

I have always been passionate about empowering organizations to unlock the full potential of their data and being part of a team that values trust, teamwork, and customer focus, and I envision myself contributing my talent to furthering NetApp's mission to be the data authority in a hybrid cloud world. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

